Acceleration: The rate of change of velocity.

Mass: The quantity of matter in an object.

Newton's Laws:

An object at rest stays at rest, and an object in motion stays in motion, unless acted upon by a force (Inertia).

Force = Mass x Acceleration (F=ma).

